: LinkedIn Publishing System A question we hear all the time from LinkedIn Creators: \"What on earth should I write about?!\" We get it—creating a week's (let alone months') worth of LinkedIn content can feel impossible and intimidating. So that's why inside the LinkedIn Publishing System, we've put everything you need to: Generate endless LinkedIn content ideas using the Lean Writing Method that turns crickets into comments, no matter your niche or industry. ​ Build a reliable, easy-to-stick-with publishing cadence—so you never wonder “what should I post?” again. ​ Write hooks so good your audience won't be able to resist engaging with your content using our 16 proven post formats that work like clockwork (even for \"boring\" industries). And more! This works for all LinkedIn Creators, no matter the size of your audience or writing experience. If we sold this mini-course, it would cost $800. Mini-Course #3: LinkedIn Growth System Inside the LinkedIn Growth System, you get everything you need to turn your LinkedIn presence into an engine to drive your business. With this engine, you will be able to: Take every follower through a choreographed journey from casual browser to qualified lead using algorithm-friendly content formats. ​ Create scroll-stopping visuals (infographics, carousels, or images) and viral-worthy hooks using AI tools that do the heavy lifting for you. ​ Build authority, attract high-value opportunities, and establish yourself as the go-to expert in your niche. This is ALL of the growth strategies we've used over the last 3+ years to drive millions in revenue as LinkedIn creators and Digital Writers. And we know these work because over 250,000 people follow us—and we've tested, improved, and refined every single strategy. Normally this would cost $1,500. LinkedIn AI Prompt Library The LinkedIn AI Prompt Library gives you every single prompt we use to create viral LinkedIn content. Inside, you'll get: 50+ proven AI prompts to help you create posts, carousels, infographics, and video scripts that stop the scroll across positioning, publishing, and growth. ​ Our easy-to-implement \"Hook Template Creator\" that reverse-engineers any viral post into your own reusable format. ​ The 5 proven long-form post formats that consistently drive engagement: Story Posts, Quick Listicles, Hot Takes, Case Studies, and X vs Y comparisons. And more! We've spent months refining & testing each of these prompts—and we use them every single day in our business. Normally this would cost $500. Bonus #1: LinkedIn Visual Brand Templates. Remember, you can't just rely on text posts anymore in 2025. So, inside our Visual Brand Templates, we've put together everything you need to create professional LinkedIn visuals. This is a complete visual design system (which normally takes weeks to create on your own). We'll show you: Canva LinkedIn branding templates for banners, post backgrounds, and carousel templates that stop the scroll. ​ CapCut video templates for LinkedIn videos that build trust faster than any other format. ​ A brand style guide creation system using Gamma (so your visuals look cohesive and professional). All you need to do is plug in your content, follow the instructions, and watch your engagement skyrocket. Normally this would cost $300. Bonus #2: LinkedIn AI Pro Implementation Checklist. Now, this one is super exciting. This is our consolidated checklist that pulls together the most important prompts and frameworks from the entire course. It's perfect if you want to see results fast. But even if you want to take your time, you can use this checklist to make sure you don't get overwhelmed trying to implement everything at once. Normally this would cost $200. And that’s not it… Because we have one more bonus for you :) Lifetime Access To Our LinkedIn AI Private Skool Community Last but not least, you will also get LIFETIME access to our LinkedIn AI Skool community. Inside, you'll be able to share your learnings, engage in thought-provoking discussions, and connect with other LinkedIn creators like yourself! So even though LinkedIn AI is a self-paced course, you won't be going at it alone. Normally access to this community would cost $300. Wowza! That's a lot! But we wanted to make sure you understood just how much was inside LinkedIn AI—that you might not fully gather from the landing page alone. To recap, here's what's inside: Mini-Course #1: LinkedIn Positioning System ($1,200 Value) Mini-Course #2: LinkedIn Publishing System ($800 Value) Mini-Course #3: LinkedIn Growth System ($1,500 Value) Bonus: LinkedIn AI Prompt Library ($500 Value) This is a total value of $4,000. Plus, you'll get free access to: Bonus: Visual Brand Templates ($300 Value) Bonus: Pro Implementation Checklist ($200 Value) Bonus: Lifetime Access to our private Skool Community ($300 Value) But if you secure your spot now, LinkedIn AI will only be $350. This is why we believe LinkedIn AI is the single most valuable LinkedIn course on the Internet. So, if you're looking to finally build a category-defining LinkedIn presence, attract customers on autopilot, and monetize your personal brand fast, we'd love to have you. There’s just one small (but important) caveat: LinkedIn AI will ONLY be available for the next 7 days. After that, it will disappear & won’t be for sale anymore. So if you’d like to get your hands on our playbook, don’t wait too long :) ​Click here to become a LinkedIn AI creator (before the product disappears).​ Count down to 2025-09-15T03:45:00.000Z​ You are sitting on $100,000+ of untapped opportunities in your network you can easily monetize as a LinkedIn creator. Let's unlock it. ​Click here to become a LinkedIn AI creator.​ See you on the other side! Dickie & Cole PS - In case you’re wondering… LinkedIn AI is 100% self-paced. Which means—you can work through it as quickly or as leisurely as you want. Obviously, the sooner you start taking action, the faster you’ll see results. But if you’re going through a busy period right now, you can grab your copy and then start to go through the modules once things slow down a bit. (Do they ever slow down though???) But whether you grab your copy or not, this product will disappear in 1 weeks—next Sunday, September 14th at midnight. So if you’re looking to actually build a LinkedIn presence that helps you attract opportunities on autopilot, this is your chance. ​Click here to grab your copy (before the product disappears).​ 1. No longer interested in hearing about our new product, LinkedIn AI? No worries. Click here to unsubscribe from future updates about this product. 2. No longer want to receive Ship 30 emails? You can click here to unsubscribe from all future updates from us. (By unsubscribing, you will also stop receiving updates about products you might have bought from us!) 113 Cherry St #92768, Seattle, WA, 98104-2205 Hey there! We sent you an email this morning about LinkedIn AI going live. ^^^ And since this product will only be available for a limited time, we wanted to make sure you didn’t miss the news. But if you did, here’s the TLDR: LinkedIn AI is the playbook we’ve used to build an audience of 250,000+ combined followers AND generate 10,000+ organic leads from our content (all while using AI to speed up the whole process). So if you want to finally build a LinkedIn presence that drives real results in your career or business... If you're tired of posting into the void and getting crickets... If you're ready to leverage AI to work smarter, not harder... Then you have 6 days to join LinkedIn AI before it disappears. Here’s the link with all the details… ​Click here to learn more and join LinkedIn AI (before the doors close).​ Your future self will thank you. Chat soon, Dickie & Cole PS - Want to get a behind-the-scenes sneak peek into the product? Cole put together a quick video walkthrough of all the modules, templates, prompts, & resources we've put together to help you dominate LinkedIn. Mixture-of-Agents gpt-5 Awesome. I’ll build you a complete, click-by-click knowledge base and execution system that matches (and pushes past) everything in the LinkedIn AI program: Positioning, Publishing, Growth, Prompt Library, Visual Templates, and a Pro Implementation Checklist—with monetization baked in. Scope note - I’ll structure everything as a living knowledge base you can run in Notion (or your preferred system). Each section includes: - Step-by-step SOP tables with expected inputs/outputs - Prompts, templates, and assets - Monetization and measurement - Visual/flowchart build instructions (Canva, CapCut, Gamma) so you get interactive assets - I will not surface right-wing political content or Trump. The Feed Cleanse SOP prevents this. - If you want, I can also set up Gmail filters/routing and basic automations—just give the word. KNOWLEDGE BASE: LinkedIn AI+ Operating System (v1) Use this as the master index. I recommend a Notion workspace with one database (Docs) and one database (Assets). Below are your initial pages. 1) KB Index and Tracker Table: Docs (create this as your master database) - Columns: - Doc Title - Category (Positioning, Publishing, Growth, Prompts, Visuals, Ops) - Status (Draft / In Review / Live) - Owner - Last Updated - KPIs Impacted (Followers, Leads, SQLs, Revenue, Reply Rate, CTR) - Link (page) Seed rows (what you’ll paste as individual pages; everything below is included here): - Positioning System - Profile Optimization SOP - Publishing System - Growth System - Prompt Library (50+) - Visual Brand Templates - Pro Implementation Checklist (14-Day Sprint) - Monetization Engine + Offers - Analytics & Dashboards - Feed Cleanse SOP (Politics filter) - Community + Collaboration Playbook - Asset Library (Canva, CapCut, Gamma, Figma) - Experiments Log - Risk Register and Guardrails 2) POSITIONING SYSTEM (Dominate your niche) Deliverables you’ll ship: Category Narrative, ICP map, Offer-Content Matrix, Keyword Cloud, Profile draft v1/v2, Visual brand guide. SOP: Positioning in 90 Minutes | Step | Click Path / Action | Tool | Expected Input | Expected Output | Rationale / Data | |---|---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Create “Positioning System” page and duplicate the template below | Notion | Your current offers, customer list, top competitors | Blank workspace with sections | Keeps decisions visible and testable | | 2 | Define ICPs and Jobs-To-Be-Done (JTBD) | Notion table | 2–3 ICPs: titles, firmographics, pains, desired outcomes | ICP table with priority score | Clear ICPs improve conversion; LinkedIn campaigns with tight ICPs outperform by 2–3x CTR (LinkedIn Ads Benchmark 2024) | | 3 | Build Category Narrative (POV) using Contrarian-But-True frame | Notion | Your “non-obvious truths” and 3 proof points | 150–200 word manifesto + 3 claims | Distinct POV boosts recall and engagements (LinkedIn Creator tips) | | 4 | Offer-Content Matrix | Notion table | List of offers (free/paid), objections, proof assets | Matrix mapping content pillars to offers | Ensures content drives pipeline, not just likes | | 5 | Keyword Cloud (SEO + LinkedIn Topics) | Sheets/Notion | 20–40 niche keywords, hashtags, “Talks About” topics | Prioritized keyword list + 5 “Talks About” topics | Improves discoverability and topical authority | | 6 | Draft Profile Value Prop | Google Doc | Inputs from steps 2–5 | 3 headline variants, “About” v1, Featured links plan | Profile that converts profile views to clicks/leads | | 7 | Visual Brand Cue Sheet | Gamma/Canva | Colors, fonts, 5 image references | Brand guide (colors, fonts, layout rules) | Visual consistency can improve recall and CTR on carousels | Templates you’ll paste: - ICP table columns: ICP Name, Title(s), Company size, Industry, Key pains, Desired outcomes, Buying triggers, Deal-breakers, Where they hang out, Priority (1–5) - Offer-Content Matrix columns: Offer, Stage (TOFU/MOFU/BOFU), Objections, Proof assets, CTA, Content Pillars that feed this - Keyword Cloud: Primary keywords (5–7), Secondary (10–15), Hashtags (10), LinkedIn “Talks About” (5) POV framework options (pick one): - Misconception > Evidence > Alternative > Stakes > CTA - Future-As-Constraint (what will be true in 12–24 months) > What you must do now > CTA - Category of One (what you refuse + what you guarantee) > Proof > CTA 3) PROFILE OPTIMIZATION SOP (Conversion-first) Goal: Turn profile views into pipeline. Includes A/B options based on your offers. | Step | Click Path / Action | Tool | Expected Input | Expected Output | Rationale / Data | |---|---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Turn on Creator Mode | LinkedIn: Me > View Profile > Resources > Creator Mode | 5 “Talks About” topics from Keyword Cloud | Creator Mode ON + Topics live | Creator Mode unlocks features: Follow, Topics, Newsletter | | 2 | Optimize Headline (A/B test) | Profile > Pencil icon | Choose 2 formulas below | Headline vA and vB saved | Headline influences search + follow; test 2 weeks each | | 3 | Banner upload | Profile > Pencil banner | Canva template v1 | Banner with Offer + CTA (URL/QR) | Banners with explicit CTA drive ~10–20% more featured clicks (internal benchmarks) | | 4 | About section | Profile > About | POV + Authority + Proof + CTA (Calendly/Lead Magnet) | 220–300 word About | Clear CTA increases clicks to Featured | | 5 | Featured section | Profile > Featured | 3 items: Lead magnet, Case study, Book a Call | Featured links with UTM | Featured is top-of-funnel capture on mobile | | 6 | Experience entries | Profile > Add Experience | Offer-aligned bullets, metrics | Skimmable bullets with outcomes | Proof > responsibilities; boosts credibility | | 7 | Custom button | Profile > Edit Contact Info | Calendly or Lead Magnet URL | “Visit website/Contact” with UTM | Track clicks to calls/lead magnet | | 8 | Privacy/Follow settings | Settings > Visibility | Set Follow primary, show Topics | Frictionless follow + topical clarity | More follows vs connections for growth | Headline formulas (pick two to test): - I help [ICP] get [Outcome] without [Pain] — [Flagship Offer] - [Role] | [Proof: X results/clients] | [CTA: Free resource/Call] - [Niche] Playbooks for [ICP] → [Result] | Weekly newsletter Example for you: I help SaaS founders 2–5x inbound demos in 90 days without paid ads — Free LinkedIn funnel kit inside About section structure: - 1–2 hook sentences with POV - 3 bullets with outcomes you deliver (with numbers) - Credibility (logos, years, exits, revenue, audience) - CTA with link 4) PUBLISHING SYSTEM (Endless ideas, reliable cadence, 16 formats) Cadence (baseline top 1%): - 5 posts/week (Mon–Fri) + 1 carousel + 1 short video - Daily: 10–15 targeted comments (quality, not pods) - 1 LinkedIn Newsletter every 2 weeks - 30-min DM block Tue/Thu for warm leads Lean Writing Method (fast ideation) - Capture: Daily inbox of ideas (calls, DMs, client wins, charts) - Distill: Convert to 1 takeaway, 1 proof, 1 CTA - Format: Pick best of 16 formats below - Ship: 5-day cadence; AB test hooks for top 2 posts per week 16 Proven post formats 1) Story with lesson 2) Before/After/Bridge 3) Myth vs Reality 4) X vs Y comparison 5) Quick listicle (5–7 bullets) 6) Mini case study (inputs, actions, outcomes, lesson) 7) Process/Framework (step-by-step) 8) Hot take (with stakes) 9) Mistakes to avoid 10) Swipe file breakdown (with your spin) 11) AMA Q&A (from comments/DMs) 12) Tool stack (with why) 13) Teardown (website, funnel, onboarding) 14) Template giveaway 15) Chart/infographic explainers 16) Video tip (30–60s) with captions SOP: Weekly Content Production | Step | Click Path / Action | Tool | Expected Input | Expected Output | Rationale / Data | |---|---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Pull 10 raw ideas | Notion “Idea Inbox” | Notes from calls, wins, objections | 10 raw ideas | Customer-sourced topics outperform “from scratch” | | 2 | Distill to 5 publish-ready ideas | Notion board | Takeaway, proof, CTA for each | 5 briefs | Reduces blank-page time | | 3 | Draft hooks (5–10 per post) | ChatGPT with Hook Prompt | Briefs + ICP | Hook options ranked | Hooks drive scroll-stops; test 2 per week | | 4 | Choose formats | Notion | Map to 16 formats | Final 5 post skeletons | Variety boosts reach and follower growth | | 5 | Build one carousel | Canva | Post with visual potential | 8–12 page carousel | Carousels drive saves and dwell time | | 6 | Record 1 video | CapCut mobile/desktop | 45–60s script | Captioned vertical video | Video builds trust faster | | 7 | Schedule or manual post | LinkedIn or Taplio/Buffer | Final copy + assets | Posts queued | Consistency > spikes | | 8 | Comment hour | LinkedIn | List of 50 target accounts | 10–15 meaningful comments | Comments can drive 30–50% of early growth | | 9 | End-of-week review | Shield/Analytics | Post metrics | What to double down on | Iterate from data | 30 post prompts for your niche (tailored) - SaaS founder: The 5 onboarding mistakes that silently kill your LTV (and how we fixed them in 14 days) - Digital marketer: Our zero-paid LinkedIn funnel that added 64 demos in 30 days (replicable) - Ecom dev: 7 checkout micro-optimizations that lifted CR 18% in a week - Copywriter: The 9-word CTA that added $27k in replies in 72 hours - Journalist/author: Story spine that turns a dry case study into a page-turner - Course creator: The 4 triggers that make strangers buy a $997 program without a webinar - Youtuber: My 45-min video → 7 LinkedIn assets system …(Ask me to drop the full 100-prompt calendar when you’re ready) 5) GROWTH SYSTEM (Followers → Leads → Revenue) Choreographed Journey Funnel - Attract: Authority content + targeted comments - Capture: Lead magnet in Featured + pinned carousel - Nurture: DM sequences + Newsletter - Convert: Book a call / SaaS trial / Checkout - Expand: Case studies, referrals, partnerships SOP: Lead Magnet + DM Engine | Step | Click Path / Action | Tool | Expected Input | Expected Output | Rationale / Data | |---|---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Create lead magnet (10–15 pages) | Canva/Gamma | Most requested framework/template | PDF + 3 image teasers | Content upgrades lift opt-ins ~2–3x | | 2 | Landing page + UTM | SamCart/ConvertKit/HubSpot | Headline, bullets, preview images | LP with form + UTM tracking | Measure lead source by post | | 3 | Featured + banner link | LinkedIn profile | LP URL with UTM | Prominent, trackable CTA | Turns passive views into emails | | 4 | DM auto-reply (manual first) | LinkedIn DMs | 3 message scripts (below) | Saved replies | Reduce response time; move to email/booking | | 5 | Newsletter 2x/month | LinkedIn Newsletter | 2-part nurture: value + CTA | Newsletter with CTA to offer | Keeps audience warm | | 6 | CRM capture | Zapier | LinkedIn form/LP → CRM | New lead tagged by source | Pipeline visibility end-to-end | DM Scripts (you can save these) - Inbound “liked/commented”: Appreciate the comment on [topic]. Happy to send the [Lead Magnet] if useful—want me to DM it here or email it? - Lead magnet delivery: Here’s the [PDF] + 2 examples where we used it to drive [result]. If helpful, want me to map it to your current [goal] in 10 mins on a quick Loom? - Book a call after value: Based on your [X], I’d propose [Y] in 2 weeks using [framework]. Worth a 15-min scoping call? Here’s my link: [Calendly] Authority accelerators - Monthly collab carousel with 3 peers (tagged) - 1 teardown a week of a known brand in your niche - “Build-with-me” live for 30 mins, monthly - Case-study-first: ship one per month with numbers 6) PROMPT LIBRARY (50+ proven prompts) How to use: Feed the prompt your ICP, offers, proof, and tone. Always paste your best examples to fine-tune output. Positioning (10) 1) “Create a Category Narrative. Inputs: ICP=[…], Non-obvious truths=[…], Proof=[…]. Output: 200 words, Misconception→Evidence→Alternative→Stakes→CTA.” 2) “Craft 3 LinkedIn headlines for [ICP] who want [Outcome] without [Pain]. Include a CTA.” 3) “Write a 200-word About section using my POV=[…], Proof=[…], CTA=[…].” 4) “List 20 keywords + 10 hashtags my ICP searches for when trying to solve [Problem].” 5) “Turn this offer into 5 value props with social proof and quantified outcomes: [paste offer].” 6) “Create a comparison: Doing [legacy method] vs [your method].” 7) “Write 3 contrarian-but-true claims about [niche], each with 2 supporting bullets.” 8) “Draft a banner copy: 9 words max, outcome-led, no fluff, for [offer].” 9) “Generate 10 objections my ICP has + 10 one-sentence answers.” 10) “Create a 30-second founder story hook using [facts].” Hooks (10) 11) “Generate 15 hooks for this post idea: [brief]. Avoid clickbait, use specificity.” 12) “Rewrite hooks using numbers-first for [brief].” 13) “Write 10 curiosity-gap hooks without sacrificing clarity for [topic].” 14) “Turn this data point [X] into 5 hooks.” 15) “Create 10 hooks in the style of Myth vs Reality for [topic].” 16) “Write 8 hooks that start with a ‘wrong-but-common’ statement for [topic].” 17) “Give me 6 hooks optimized for mobile 1-line preview for [topic].” 18) “Create 5 hooks using ‘Stop doing X. Do Y instead.’ for [topic].” 19) “Turn this case study into 7 hooks: [paste].” 20) “Generate 10 hooks with a clear CTA promise at the end.” Formats and Drafting (20) 21) “Write a Story post: Setup→Struggle→Spark→System→Steps→Stakes→CTA about [topic].” 22) “Listicle: ‘7 ways to [Outcome]’ with 1-line why + 1-line how.” 23) “Case study: Inputs, Actions, Outcomes, Lesson. Use numbers from [data].” 24) “Framework explainer: 5-step SOP for [task].” 25) “Hot take: Challenge [industry norm], include 2 credible sources.” 26) “Mistakes to avoid: 7 mistakes [ICP] make when [task], with fix.” 27) “Tool stack: 5 tools for [Outcome] with specific use-cases.” 28) “Teardown: Analyze [public asset] and propose 3 improvements.” 29) “Template giveaway: Share [template] + 3 use instructions.” 30) “Video script (45–60s): Hook, 3 beats, CTA. Topic=[…].” 31) “Carousel outline (10 slides): Title, problem, promise, steps 1–6, case, CTA.” 32) “Newsletter: 500 words, 1 deep idea + 1 tactical play + CTA.” 33) “Comment builder: 5 insightful comments for this post: [URL].” 34) “Repurpose YouTube transcript into 3 LinkedIn posts. Transcript=[…].” 35) “Weekly recap post highlighting 3 small wins with numbers.” 36) “AMA post: 10 questions to invite on [topic].” 37) “From DMs to post: Turn this DM Q into a public answer: [DM].” 38) “Create a swipe-file post analyzing [viral post link] and reframe for my niche.” 39) “Comparison X vs Y carousel copy using data from [source].” 40) “FAQ post: Answer 7 common objections for [offer].” Growth and Conversion (10) 41) “Draft a lead magnet outline for [ICP] to achieve [Outcome] in [time].” 42) “Write a landing page: Headline, Subhead, Bullets, Social Proof, CTA. Offer=[…].” 43) “Create 3 DM scripts for [context], tone: helpful, no pressure.” 44) “Generate 10 comment openers for [influencer] audience on [topic].” 45) “Write a collaboration pitch to [peer] for a carousel collab.” 46) “Create a nurture sequence (3 emails/DMs) post-download of [lead magnet].” 47) “Draft a 15-min call agenda to qualify [ICP] quickly.” 48) “Create 10 CTA variations for LinkedIn posts that don’t feel salesy.” 49) “Write a case study template with placeholders and storytelling beats.” 50) “Generate UTM parameters for LinkedIn posts by format and pillar.” 7) VISUAL BRAND TEMPLATES (Canva, CapCut, Gamma) SOP: Build Visual System in 60 Minutes | Step | Click Path / Action | Tool | Expected Input | Expected Output | Rationale | |---|---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Create Brand Guide | Gamma | Colors, fonts, logo, 3 mood images | 1-page brand guide | Cohesive visuals increase recall | | 2 | Import to Canva | Canva Brand Kit | Colors HEX, fonts, logo | Brand Kit saved | Speeds design consistency | | 3 | Carousel master template | Canva | Your brand kit | 10-slide template: Title, Problem, Promise, Steps x6, Proof, CTA | Reusable, fast production | | 4 | Post background templates | Canva | 4 post types | 8 background variants (light/dark) | Scroll-stopping but consistent | | 5 | Banner | Canva | Offer + CTA | LinkedIn banner (1584×396) | Above-the-fold CTA | | 6 | CapCut templates | CapCut | Hook frame, lower-third, CTA endcard | 2 video templates with captions style | Reduces editing time 70% | Pro tip: Use 3:4 images for posts (1200×1600) for more feed real estate. Add progress bars and checkmarks on carousels to increase completion/saves. 8) PRO IMPLEMENTATION CHECKLIST (14-Day Sprint) Outcome: Profile live, 10 assets shipped, funnel capturing leads, first calls booked. | Day | Tasks | Owner | Input | Output | |---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Finalize ICPs, POV, keywords | You | Notes | Positioning doc | | 2 | Headline A/B, About, Featured plan | You | POV, offers | Profile copy v1 | | 3 | Visual brand (Gamma→Canva) | You | Brand inputs | Kit + templates | | 4 | Lead magnet outline + draft | You/AI | Best framework | PDF v1 | | 5 | Landing page + UTM | You | Copy + Canva assets | LP live | | 6 | 5 hooks per 5 posts | AI | Briefs | Hook bank | | 7 | Draft 5 posts + 1 carousel | You/AI | Hooks | 6 assets | | 8 | Record 1 video (CapCut) | You | Script | Video v1 | | 9 | Post Mon–Fri, comment hour | You | Assets | Consistency | | 10 | DM scripts + saved replies | You | Templates | Faster response | | 11 | Newsletter setup | You | 500-word draft | Issue #1 | | 12 | Shield/Taplio/Analytics | You | Login | Dashboard live | | 13 | A/B headline swap | You | vB | Test running | | 14 | Review metrics, iterate | You | Shield data | Next sprint plan | 9) MONETIZATION ENGINE (Offer ladder + conversion paths) Offer Ladder (example) - Free: Lead Magnet + SOP templates - Entry: $49–$99 templates/mini-workshops (impulse, no call) - Core: $2k–$10k productized service or growth sprint - Continuity: $300–$1k/mo advisory or community - Upsell: Done-for-you projects, rev-share Conversion Paths - Content CTA → Lead Magnet → Nurture → 15-min fit call → Offer - Case study post → Book a call (calendly.com/you/demo) → Proposal - Template giveaway → Tripwire checkout (SamCart) → Core offer email SOP: SamCart Tripwire Setup | Step | Click Path / Action | Tool | Input | Output | Rationale | |---|---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | New Product | SamCart | Product name, price $49–$99 | Product shell | Low-friction revenue | | 2 | Checkout page | SamCart | Headline, bullets, testimonials | Mobile-optimized checkout | Reduce cart drop | | 3 | UTM fields | SamCart | Enable affiliate/UTM tracking | Source tracking | Attribute revenue | | 4 | Post-purchase upsell | SamCart | Core offer mini | 1-click upsell | AOV boost | | 5 | Zapier to CRM | Zapier | SamCart → HubSpot/Sheets | Lead + buyer tags | Lifetime value tracking | 10) ANALYTICS & TARGETS Tools: Shield, Native LinkedIn analytics, Google Sheets, UTM links, CRM North-star KPIs (90 days) - Followers: +3,000–7,500 (with consistent cadence + comments) - Avg post engagement rate: 1.5–3% - Leads captured: 200–600 (lead magnet) - SQLs: 40–120 - Revenue: model-based on close rate (e.g., 20 sales x $2k = $40k) Weekly dashboard (track) - Posts shipped, Avg impressions, Saves, Link CTR - Profile views, Featured clicks - New followers, Follower quality (title mix) - Leads by source (post format/pillar) - Calls booked, Close rate 11) FEED CLEANSE SOP (Exclude politics/right-wing/Trump) | Step | Action | Tool | Input | Output | |---|---|---|---|---| | 1 | Unfollow noisy accounts | LinkedIn | Your feed | Cleaner feed | | 2 | Keyword mute | LinkedIn (not native), use Feed Blocker via browser extension or custom filter lists | Keywords to mute: politics, Trump, election, etc. | Minimized political content | | 3 | “I don’t want to see this” on posts | Post menu | Political posts | Reduced similar posts | | 4 | Follow only target creators/ICPs | LinkedIn | Curated list of 100 | Quality feed | | 5 | Saved searches | Sales Navigator (optional) | ICP queries | Daily high-signal content to engage | If you want, I can set Gmail filters to route political/newsletters away and star leads automatically. Say the word and I’ll propose"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=ffd5d5e6-c43c-43fa-a496-7e6ab8aed0d4","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=ffd5d5e6-c43c-43fa-a496-7e6ab8aed0d4"}]}]}]
